I have found some inconsistent behaviour with objects. I believe this is an issue with decoder.py, I looked into it but couldn't make sense of it. (Document obscure param names & methods please?)

Valid:
```
{
  admin: {
    os: {
      get: [id, name, version, servers]
      put: [name, version, servers]
      post: true
      delete: true}
...
```

Valid:
```
{
  admin: {
    os: {
      get: [id name version servers]
      put: [name version servers]
      post: true
      delete: true}
...
```

Valid:
```
{
  admin: {
    os: {
      get: [
        id,
        name,
        version,
        servers
      ]
      put: [
        name,
        version,
        servers
      ]
      post: true
      delete: true
    }
...
```
Invalid:
```
{
  admin: {
    os: {
      get: [id name version servers]
      put: [name version servers]
      post: true
      delete: true
    }
...
```

Is this hjson snippet meant to deserialize?

// loads() throws
{
  name: test
  nested: { foo: one }
}

Note that the following forms do not throw:

// works
{
  name: test
  nested: { foo: 1 }
}

// works
{
  name: test
  nested: { foo: "one" }
}

Thanks
